msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:121
msgid "Colored Gray"
msgstr "色付きグレー"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:123
msgid "Neutral Gray"
msgstr "中間のグレー"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:130
msgid ".. image:: /images/color_category/Cmyk_black_differences.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:130
msgid ""
"In Krita, there's also the fact that the default color is a perfect black in "
"RGB, which then gets converted to our default CMYK in a funny manner, giving "
"a yellow look to the strokes. Again, another good reason to work in RGB and "
"let the conversion be done by the printing house."
msgstr ""
"Krita では既定色は RGB の完全な黒で、そこから CMYK に変換されるため、黄色がか"
"かった少々おかしい色になります。もう一度繰り返しますが、RGB で作業するべきも"
"う一つの理由はそうした変換を印刷所で行ってもらえることです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:132
msgid ""
"While CMYK has a smaller 'gamut' than RGB, however, it's still recommended "
"to use an RGB working space profile to do your editing in. Afterwards, you "
"can convert it to your printer's CMYK profile using either perceptual or "
"relative colorimetric intent. Or you can just give the workspace rgb image "
"to your printer and let them handle the work."
msgstr ""
"CMYK が RGB よりも'色域'が少ない中でも、RGB 作業空間プロファイルを使って編集"
"することが望まれます。最後に知覚的、もしくは相対的な色彩意図に基づいてプリン"
"タの CMYK プロファイルを使って変換することができます。または作業に使った RGB "
"画像を単にプリンタにそのまま渡しプリンタに任せることもできます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:138
msgid "YCrCb"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:140
msgid "Luminosity, Red-chroma, Blue-chroma"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:142
msgid "YCrCb stands for:"
msgstr "YCrCb は次の略です:"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:144
msgid "Y'/Y"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:145
msgid "Luma/Luminosity, thus, the amount of light a color reflects."
msgstr "ルーマ/輝度、つまり、色に反映される明るさの量です。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:146
msgid "Cr"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:147
msgid ""
"Red Chroma. This value measures how red a color is versus how green it is."
msgstr "赤の彩度。どれだけ赤か緑かを示します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:149
msgid "Cb"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:149
msgid ""
"Blue Chroma. This value measures how blue a color is versus how yellow it is."
msgstr "青の彩度。どれだけ青か黄色かを示します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:151
msgid ""
"This color space is often used in photography and in (correct) "
"implementations of JPEG. As a human you're much more sensitive to the "
"lightness of colors, and thus JPEG tries to compress the Cr and Cb channels, "
"and leave the Y channel in full quality."
msgstr ""
"この色空間はしばしば写真や JPEG の(正しい)実装で使われます。人間であれば色の"
"明るさにより感受性が高いため、JPEG は Cr と Cb チャネルを圧縮し、Yチャネルは"
"元の品質を保持します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:156
msgid "XYZ"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:158
msgid ""
"Back in 1931, the CIE (Institute of Color and Light), was studying human "
"color perception. In doing so, they made the first color spaces, with XYZ "
"being the one best at approximating human vision."
msgstr ""
"遡ること1931年、CIE(国際照明委員会)は人の色知覚を調べていました。その中で最初"
"の色空間を作り、XYZ が最も人の目に合ったものであるとされました。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:161
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "XYZ is used as a baseline reference for all other profiles and models. "
#| "All color conversions are done in XYZ, and all profiles coordinates match "
#| "XYZ."
msgid ""
"XYZ is used as a baseline reference for all other profiles and models. All "
"color conversions are done in XYZ, and all profiles coordinates match XYZ. "
"An RGB color space where Red is set to 100% X, Green is set to 100% Y and "
"Blue is set to 100% Z, with the gamma correction being linear is in effect "
"the same as an XYZ color space."
msgstr ""
"XYZ は他のすべてのプロファイルやモデルの元として使われるものです。すべての色"
"変換は XYZ で行われ、すべてのプロファイルは XYZ 座標に適合します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:166
msgid "L\\*a\\*b\\*"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:168
msgid ""
"A Color space based on the opposition theory of color vision, L\\*a\\*b\\* "
"splits colors into the luminosity, red-green contrast and blue-yellow "
"contrast:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:170
msgid "L\\*"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:171
msgid "Lightness, similar to luminosity in this case."
msgstr "明度、この場合は光度に近いです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:172
msgid "a\\*"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:173
msgid ""
"a\\* in this case is the measurement of how magenta a color is versus how "
"green it is."
msgstr "この場合の a\\* は色がどれだけマゼンタか緑かです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:175
msgid "b\\*"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:175
msgid ""
"b\\* in this case is a measurement of how yellow a color is versus how blue "
"a color is."
msgstr "この場合の b\\* は色がどれだけ黄色か青かです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:177
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "L\\*a\\*b\\* is supposed to be a more comprehensible variety of XYZ and "
#| "the most 'complete' of all color spaces. It's often used as an in between "
#| "color space in conversion, but even more as the correct color space to do "
#| "color-balancing in. It's far easier to adjust the contrast and color tone "
#| "in L*a*b*."
msgid ""
"L\\*a\\*b\\* is supposed to be a more comprehensible to use that XYZ. It's "
"often used as an in between color space in conversion, but even more as the "
"correct color space to do color-balancing in. It's far easier to adjust the "
"contrast and color tone in L*a*b*."
msgstr ""
"L\\*a\\*b\\* は XYZ より包括的で、すべての色空間の中で最も'完成'されたものと"
"して作られました。色空間同士の変換でしばしば使われますが、色のバランスを取り"
"ながら色空間を補正するのに向いています。色合いやコントラストの調整には "
"L*a*b* を使う方がはるかに簡単です。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:179
msgid ""
"L\\*a\\*b\\* is technically the same as Photoshop's LAB. Photoshop "
"specifically uses CIELAB d50."
msgstr ""
"L\\*a\\*b\\* は技術的には Photoshop の LAB と同一です。Photoshop は特に "
"CIELAB d50 を使用しています。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:182
msgid "Filters and blending modes"
msgstr "フィルタと合成モード"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../general_concepts/colors/color_models.rst:184
msgid ""
"Maybe you have noticed that blending modes in LAB don't work like they do in "
"RGB or CMYK. This is because the blending modes work by doing a bit of maths "
"on the color coordinates, and because color coordinates are different per "
"color space, the blending modes look different."
msgstr ""
"LAB では RGB や CMYK のように合成モードが機能しないことに気付きましたでしょう"
"か。これは合成モードが色座標の計算によって行われ、それは色空間によって異なる"
"ために合成モードは異なった見た目になります。"

#. +> trunk5
